value.0: Congratulations, you found the doomscribe.    This obviously older woman is sitting at a desk with tomes already starting to pile up as she records the deaths of those who have fallen in the area that is now under her jurisdiction. You see no hair poking from beneath her head covering because like others who are doomscribes, she has shaved her head. Like others of her order, she wears robes of gray, and she chooses to make them fashionable by layering colors of gray. With her obvious age, you wonder how long it will be before Jergal comes to mummify her so she can continue her duties.  Her skeleton servants are sanctioned undead, and assist her with the ordering of the books on the shelves that fill the room.

Value.value: Oh, you discovered me. We normally don't go among the people.
Leave my servants alone, they are sanctioned by my order. .
The skeletons here are warded against scrying so the Kelemvor priest leaves us alone. What he doesn't know won't hurt him.
If you wish to leave, just touch the bookshelf you came through to come in.

Jergal doesn't always agree with Kelemvor, but does serve him. He thinks some are worthy to continue work for him after they have died, in spite of Kelemvor's reluctance to use them. Do you think Doomscribes grow on trees?.
Death is a solemn undertaking. *a wry smile*
We are now under way. *gestures around the shrine*
You don't like my sense of humor?  I have been told it will be the death of me.
Death is but part of life: fear it not, evade it not, and view it not as evil. To fear death delivers you into the hands of those who can bring death down upon you.

Die with dignity, neither raging nor seeking to embrace undeath. Do honor to the dead, for their strivings in life brought Faerun to where it is now, and to forget them is to forget also where we are nowand why.

value.0: Doomscribe Silversmith is one of those Doomscribes that didn't know when to quit.  He has been serving Jergal for eons now.  He appears to be keeping a record of the records.  Bureaucracy at its finest.
A book in the hand is worth two on the shelf!
An ordinary lantern, such as might be found in a farmyard.  Still, it does the trick.

This is Doomscribe Minerson, a Doomscribe who didn't know when to quit.  He is still assisting in the upkeep of the records for those who have passed.  He appears to be looking for something on the shelves.
An ordinary lantern, such as might be found in a farmyard.  Still, it does the trick.
